  "text": "As an alternative strategy, the joint precoding of user messages can also be performed at the cloud server, rather than at the individual BSs. In this case, the precoded analog signals are compressed and forwarded to the corresponding BSs over the finite-capacity backhaul links for direct transmission by the BS antennas. This approach, called pure compression in this paper, is akin to the compress-and-forward relaying strategy. This approach has been investigated in [CITATION_1] , also in [CITATION_2] where the effect of imperfect channel state information (CSI) is taken into account, and more recently in [CITATION_3] , where the benefit of joint compression across multiple BSs is explored.",
